&lt;crosspost&gt; <br>
Theres no reason to play a skald past rank 5. <br>
They get no return for their RA points, and raising rank does far less useful things for them than other classes. <br>
A Zerker gains a realm rank, they get +Axe(damage) and +LeftAxe(more damage). <br>
Same for an Armsman/Paladin using an advanced weapon spec. <br>
A Minstrel gains a realm rank, they get +Instruments(better pets) and +Stealth, along with their weapon. <br>
The list continues. <br>
A Skald gets +Weapon, which isn't even worth 3/4 of what it is to another fighting class, because you get less weaponskill for the same spec, because we have Rogue weaponskill, and because Twohanders in Midgard don't scale properly for style damage. <br>
Then we get +Battlesongs, totally useless. <br>
And then finally we get +Parry, but since we don't have the spec to take parry high, its never going to be meaningful, plus logs prove that, like weapon, each point of parry does less for a Skald than it does for another fighting class, because we have Rogue weaponskill. <br>
The trend continues. <br>
When I purchase toughness, I'm getting less HPs than a tank. When I buy Mastery of Pain, I'm getting less damage too. All around, I'm getting less return for my RA points spent, while my IP and Purge RAs still cost full price. I could instead put those points towards my class specific RA, but its worse than me specline damage add, which is inturn worse than a wizard/theurgists baseline damage add. <br>
Also in high end RvR, when you're trying to protect your casters and healers, your opposing tanks will have full resists, around 50%, alogn with Determination 3-4, making your 29 second single target mez less than 9 seconds. <br>
Its these reasons why we are routinely told not to even enter combat, attack, mez, or shout in high level squads, even with a million or more RPs under our belts. <br>
Your shouts don't even land 60% of the time with those kinds of resists either. <br>
Hyrbids need new RAs, ones that allow them to focus themselves towards their caster abilties or their tank abilities. An RA that raised Weaponskill by 3% per level would help greatly. An RA that allowed our shouts to crit would help some as well. These RAs need to be cheap, much like Determination is for a pure tank, to make up for their lack of CC. <br>
I'd run at Healer speed in exchange for abilities that worked, abilities that added to a group rather than slow it down. <br>
